------------------------------------------------------------
EXECUTION LOG
------------------------------------------------------------
$ npm start → Compiled successfully! → http://localhost:3000

------------------------------------------------------------
API CALL
------------------------------------------------------------
  URL   : https://api.randomuser.me/
  Method: GET
  Called in: componentDidMount()
  Response: JSON with results[0] containing user data

------------------------------------------------------------
COMPONENT LIFECYCLE
------------------------------------------------------------
  1. constructor()       → state: { user:null, loading:true }
  2. render()            → shows spinner "Fetching user..."
  3. componentDidMount() → fetch('https://api.randomuser.me/')
     → .then(res => res.json())
     → .then(data => setState({ user: data.results[0], loading:false }))
  4. render()            → displays user card with:
       - name.title + name.first + name.last
       - picture.large  (profile image)
       - email, phone, location.city, dob.age

